# Frameworks/ — DJI Mobile SDK V5 drop-in
#
# The DJI Mobile SDK ships as a binary XCFramework and is NOT checked into
# this repo (proprietary, ~350 MB). CI builds the companion app in "stub
# mode" where `#if DJI_SDK_AVAILABLE` branches degrade to logging stubs.
#
# To light up the real SDK locally:
#
#   1. Register for a free DJI developer account at
#      https://developer.dji.com and create an app entry with bundle id
#      `com.skyherd.companion`.
#   2. Download the latest iOS Mobile SDK V5 (tested against v5.11+) from
#      https://developer.dji.com/mobile-sdk/ .
#   3. Extract `DJISDK.xcframework` and place it DIRECTLY INSIDE THIS
#      DIRECTORY so the path becomes:
#         ios/SkyHerdCompanion/Frameworks/DJISDK.xcframework
#   4. Uncomment the framework dependency in `project.yml`:
#         - framework: Frameworks/DJISDK.xcframework
#           embed: true
#   5. Set `SKYHERD_SWIFT_FLAGS = DJI_SDK_AVAILABLE` in
#      `SupportingFiles/Config.xcconfig` (copy from the template).
#   6. Re-run `./bootstrap.sh` to regenerate the Xcode project with the
#      framework linked.
#
# This .gitkeep exists solely to ensure the empty directory is tracked so
# `FRAMEWORK_SEARCH_PATHS` resolves on a fresh clone (Phase 7.2 audit fix).
